Description: An ordinary farmer. Working the land has not prepared him for the trials he is destined to face.
As war gripped his land he was conscripted into the army. He really doesn't want to be here.
Better than nothing
A gifted visionary known for predicting the future. When summoned, look at the top 3 cards in your deck and replace them in any order you desire.
A being said to be capable of speaking things into existence. When summoned, look at the top 3 cards in your opponents deck and replace them in any order you desire.
A wizard capable of venturing to the land beyond and bringing back that which was lost. Add one card from your graveyard to your hand when this Hero is Summoned.
A notoriously studious individuals who is said to know all. Pick 1 card from your opponents hand or field to view each turn.

A mysterious figure who keeps mostly to the shadows. Their identity and machinations are unknown even to the most devout of lorekeepers. You may replace one card in your hand with a random card from your Deck once per turn.
A sorcerer whose tampering with the Forbidden Arts has led him down a dark path. He frequently clashes with the White Sage. Steal one magic card from your opponents deck when Summoned.

A paragon of light whose shining example has been an inspiration for many Apprentices that came after him. He frequently clashes with the Dark Sage. Select one Magic card from your deck and add it to your hand when Summoned.
The original Grand Elder who guided his people out of the Dark Ages. If you have an activatable Tech card you may play it for free the turn this Hero is Summoned.
He has spent lifetimes taking the very concept of strength further than any before him. He's still seeking something more. Cannot be destroyed by Battle.
Rebirth: Player can choose to immediately reshuffle the cards from their Medical Bay back into their Main Deck when this card is summoned.

Never Lost A Battle: Add a Token to this card when summoned and anytime this card defeats an enemy Fighter by Battle. Anytime this card would have its Health reduced to zero, remove a Token from this card and restore Health back to original value. This card cannot be defeated by Battle until its Health is zero and it has no remaining Tokens attached to it.
When in the Reinforcement Zone, at the start of every Battle Phase, Darwin can increase the Attack of the Player's current Fighter by +1.

While this card remains on the field all Summon Crest dice rolls gain a +1 bonus. During the End Phase, add 1 Token to the Player's total. When this card is removed from the field decrease the Player's summon crests by an amount equal to the Token count.

Player may summon as many Mongol cards as they can fill in the open Reinforcement slots upon summoning this card. While this card remains on the field, Mongol reinforcements can also serve in the role of the Fighter and target any opposing Fighter or Reinforcement card for attack. Player's Ranged Attribute cards gain +1 Attack while this card is on the Field
Nihilism: Half of the damage inflicted by this card is reflected back on itself.
While this card remains in either Player's Medical Bay, boost the Attack stat of the card's original owner by +1.
Decreases the Summon Cost of any of the Player's Summoned or Activated cards by 1 while on the field.
Name one Attribute. Both Players can only summon Normal/Hero cards of that Attribute as long as this card remains on the field.

I am not a crook: When this card is summoned, your opponent must attempt to guess the name of the card at the bottom of your Medical Bay. If they guess correctly, your current fighter loses half their original attack and health stat. Otherwise the Player may draw any card from either player's Main Deck, Medical Bay, or Graveyard and put it in your hand.

When summoned the Player has the option to add Merlin and/or the Knights of the Round Table from their Deck or Hand to any open Reinforcement slot on the player's side of the field. Additionally, equip Excalibur from Deck or Hand. Card Costs are ignored.

When reinforcing King Arthur roll a pair of dice at the beginning of the Battle Phase. If the sum of the roll is at least 8, King Arthur becomes immune from taking battle damage for the remainder of the Phase.
Can be Fusion Summoned on top of any other card whose name is "Knight of the Round Table". The Attack and Health stat of the newly summoned card is added to that of the card it was fused with.
Player gains +1 Life Point per Turn while on the field.
Fighter gains +1 Health per Turn while this card remains on the field in a Reinforcement slot.
Loses 3 Health during the End Phase of the Player's Turn.
Gains 2 Attack per Turn while on the field.
Pilgrimage to Mecca: At the start of the Game, the original Owner of this card gains 20 Summon Crests.
Proletariat-Focused: When summoned, the opponent's fighter's current attack and health become equal to your fighter's current attack and health.
Boosts the Attack of all Ranged allies by +2 while on the field.
Red Fever: Reduce the health of all enemies by 5 when Lenin is summoned
Unyielding: When Churchill is on the field and one of your fighters is defeated, roll a die. If you roll a 4 or higher, put your defeated fighter in your own Medical Bay instead of your opponent's.
Imitation Game: Once per Turn, the Player may choose one Hero card on the field, Medical Bay, or Graveyard. Imitate it's effect.
The Player may resurrect 1 card from the Graveyard/Junkyard per Turn during the Standby Phase.

Zeus' attacks damage all enemy cards on the field. If sharing the field with another Olympian, Zeus can strike from any position on the field. In the event that another Olympian on the Player's field is defeating while Zeus is in play, target a random card from your Opponent's hand and add it to your Medical Bay.
Ares gains Attack and Health equal to the combined amount of his Reinforcements during the Battle Phase.
Lowers the Attack of Opposing Fighter by -2 while on the field.
All Equip cards gain +3 to the appropriate stat while Hephaestus is on the field.
Rage Against the Dying of the Light: Upon being defeated, Cronos spawns 1 Giant Attribute card from the Player's Deck in his place on the field.
Player gains access to the Fire Technology Card when Prometheus is summoned (Activate Tech Card requirements are ignored).
When summoned the Player will choose to view either the top 3 cards in their Main Deck or the top 3 cards in their Opponents Main Deck. Replace them in any order the Player desires.
Gorgon's Eye: Roll a pair of dice whenver the Opponent summons a new Fighter to the field. If the total of the dice roll is below 7, the opposing Fighter is immediately sent to the Medical bay.
When summoned the Opponent must reveal their hand to the Player.
Returns to the Player's Hand during the End Phase. Summon crests used to play this card is restored upon resolving this effect.
This card cannot be destroyed by Battle. It gains 2 Health per Turn while on the field.
When this card is defeated, the Player may capture one Magic or Trap card from the Opponent's Medical Bay and add it to their Hand.
When summoned the Player may steal one Equip card from the Opponent's field, Medical Bay, Deck, or Hand and add it to their Fighter.
Once per Turn, the player may revive one card from either Player's Medical Bay or Graveyard and activate it on their field.
Once per Turn, flip a coin. If the result is Heads, heal one of the cards on your field for +5 health. If the result is tails, inflict 5 points of damage on the opposing Fighter.

When sharing the field with King Arthur, gains +1 Attack. During the Standby Phase of the Player's Turn, roll a die. If the result is 1 or 6, Lancelot enters a state of "madness" over Guinevere and gains +3 Attack, but cannot Attack during the Battle Phase this Turn.

If King Arthur is defeated while this card is on the field, immediately send this card to the Opponent's Medical Bay. When this card is played by someone other than the original Owner, all Fighter and Reinforcement cards (excluding this one) lose 3 Health at the start of each Standby Phase. If King Arthur is summoned by the Opponent, add this card to your side of the field.
Once per turn, you may choose one Set card on the opponent's side of the field and view it. If it's a Trap card, dismantle and capture it.
Grants +1 to the Attack stat of a Normal or Hero card that the Player controls.
Grants +2 to the Attack stat of a Normal or Hero card that the Player controls.
Grants +3 to the Attack stat of your Fighter.
Can only be Equipped to "King Arthur." All currently active allied Warriors gain +2 Attack. All currently active enemy Warriors lose -3 Attack.
Grants +3 to the Attack stat of a Normal or Hero Ranged-Type card that the Player controls.
Grants +4 to the Attack stat of a Normal or Hero Ranged-Type card that the Player controls.
Grants +5 to the Attack stat of a Normal or Hero Ranged-Type card that the Player controls.
Grants +6 to the Attack stat of a Normal or Hero Ranged-Type card that the Player controls.
Grants +7 to the Attack stat of a Normal or Hero Scientist-Type card that the Player controls.
The next Normal/Hero card you Summon gets +3 Attack.
A Normal/Hero card of your choosing gains +1 Attack.
Your Normal/Hero card gain +5 Attack. When this card leaves the field your Normal/Hero cards lose -8 Attack.
Add one Equip Attribute Magic card from your Graveyard/Junkyard to your hand.
The Cost of Magic cards is reduced by 1 for the Player.
Discard 1 card to the Graveyard/Junkyard. You win the Battle this round.

Roll a six-sided dice and apply the result:
 1: Skip the Battle Phase. You lose the Battle this round.
 2-5: ???
 6: Skip the Battle Phase. You win the Battle this round.
Revive one card from either Player's Graveyard/Junkyard and add it to your hand. Upon resolving this card's effect, banish it.
Choose one card from either player's Medical Bay to heal and add it to your hand.
Inflict 5 Life Points of Damage to the Opponent.
Switch decks with your opponent (Med Bays are not switched). Your opponent gets to take 1 card from your hand (or field if no cards are in your hand) and add it to their own hand.
When your opponent activates a Tech Card, play this card to force them to skip their next Draw during the Opening Phase.
If your opponent's Fighter has more attack strength than your Fighter you may activate this card; Your Fighter gains +7 Attack.
When equipped to your Fighter you may inflict Paralysis on the currently active opposing Fighter.
Upon inflicting Life Point damage on the Opponent, they must discard their entire hand to the Graveyard/Junkyard/Medical Bay as appropriate.
Activate when to Opponent summons a new Fighter to the field. The Fighter is immediately captured and sent to the Player's Medical Bay.
All Player's Normal and Hero cards immediately gain +5 Health when summoned for the remainder of the game.
The Opponent must re-roll any dice roll that results in a total greater than '4.'
Duplicates the effect of one of the Opponent's active Tech cards. If Opponent has multiple Tech cards active, the Player can choose which card to mimic.
Permanently increases your Summon Crest Rolls by +1.
Permanently decreases your Summon Cost of cards by -1.
Enhances the impact of your stat boosting card effects by +1.
Enhances the effectiveness of your Equip cards by +1.
Increases the Health of all your Normal and Hero cards by +3 at the start of each Standby Phase.
When activated select one of your opponent's Equip card slots and disable it.
Both Players must draw the top card from their Tech Deck and Activate it in their Tech Zone.
